Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.003
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places

    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0

function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(num) {
  if (Math.abs(num) < 0.05) {
    return 0; // Round very small values near zero to 0
  } else if (num < 10) {
    return Math.round(num * 100) / 100; // Round to two decimal places
  } else {
    return Math.round(num); // Round to the nearest integer
  }
}
